 2. Keywords
 
 3.1. Normal identifiers
 
 Identifiers start with a letter, a dollar or an underscore. They cannot start with a number.
 
Here are a few examples of valid identifiers (here, variable names):

def name
def item3
def with_underscore
def $dollarStart

But the following ones are invalid identifiers:

def 3tier
def a+b
def a#b

Naming Variables

Live Demo
class Example { 
   static void main(String[] args) { 
      // Defining a variable in lowercase  
      int x = 5;
	  
      // Defining a variable in uppercase  
      int X = 6; 
	  
      // Defining a variable with the underscore in it's name 
      def _Name = "Joe"; 
		
      println(x); 
      println(X); 
      println(_Name); 
   } 
}


Printing Variables


class Example { 
   static void main(String[] args) { 
      //Initializing 2 variables 
      int x = 5; 
      int X = 6; 
	  
      //Printing the value of the variables to the console 
      println("The value of x is " + x );  
   }
}

Arithmetic Operators
+ - / * % ++ --
Relational operators
== != < <= > >=
Logical Operators
&& || !
Assignment operators
+= -= *= /= %= 
def A = 5
A+=3
Output will be 8 (Smilar for Others)

Range Operators
def range = 0..5 
class Example { 
   static void main(String[] args) { 
      def range = 5..10; 
      println(range); 
      println(range.get(2)); 
   } 
}

Result:

[5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10] 
7

The while statement is executed by first evaluating the condition expression (a Boolean value), and if the result is true, then the statements in the while loop are executed. The process is repeated starting from the evaluation of the condition in the while statement.

while(condition) { 
   statement #1 
   statement #2 
   ... 
}

class Example {
   static void main(String[] args) {
      int count = 0;
		
      while(count<5) {
         println(count);
         count++;
      }
   }
   
   
}

For Loop 

Live Demo
class Example { 
   static void main(String[] args) {
	
      for(int i = 0;i<5;i++) {
         println(i);
      }
		
   }
}

For-in

for(variable in range) { 
   statement #1 
   statement #2 
   â€¦ 
}


class Example { 
   static void main(String[] args) { 
      int[] array = [0,1,2,3]; 
		
      for(int i in array) { 
         println(i); 
      } 
   } 
}

Live Demo
class Example {
   static void main(String[] args) {
	
      for(int i in 1..5) {
         println(i);
      }
		
   } 
} 

Live Demo
class Example {
   static void main(String[] args) {
      def employee = ["Ken" : 21, "John" : 25, "Sally" : 22];
		
      for(emp in employee) {
         println(emp);
      }
   }
}
